		<h4>THE SCRIPT</h4>
		<p>For the script, I gave a high-level conceptual of the BIG JAMBOX product. At that point, nobody knew what the product was. Using a product code name, I told them that it was a portable speaker that was slightly larger than the current JAMBOX. It would have a few more controls, with some staying in the same locations, like: the pairing button, the On/Off switch, and the audio jack.</p>
		<p>I then showed them two possible prototypes for the controls, Option A and Option B. For half the users, I switched the order to somewhat randomize ther results.</p>
	</div>
</div>

