<div class="text-block row">
	<div class="large-8 columns large-offset-2">
		<p>My main questions were to understand if the users understood the functionality of each of the buttons. If they didn't understand what the button did, I would tell them, and then ask what would have made more sense.</p>
		<p>Most of the controls turned out to be straightforward, but the biggest question was if users could understand how to mute. I gauged this by giving them a following scenario, and seeing which control they gravitated towards:
			<ul>
				<li>Someone calls you – which button do you hit?</li>
				<li>You need to mute the conversation – which button do you hit?</li>
				<li>You need to end the call – which button do you hit?</li>
			</ul>
		</p>
	</div>
</div>

